JSConfigs API Reference

Each ServiceStack Route will be listed with it's Return Type, which Verbs (aka Methods) are allowed to be used with it, the url path for the endpoint, notes entered by the developer in the code, a summary of the purpose of the endpoint, the data that the endpoint can take in (parameters) as well as the Return Type's properties (if an object model) and an example of how to call it in TypeScript.

ClearJSConfigsCaches
DELETE | Returns: CEFActionResponse | Path: /JSConfigs/ClearCaches

Clears the caches for the JSConfigs endpoints

Takes in the following parameters

Name Data Type Parameter Type Required Description

TypeScript Example

this.cvApi.jSConfigs.ClearJSConfigsCaches().then(r => {
	if (!r || !r.data) {
		// Error State
		return;
	}
	this.something = r.data;
}).catch(reason => console.error(reason));

UpdateAppSettings
POST | Returns: CEFActionResponse | Path: /JSConfigs/UpdateAppSettings

Update the app settings values to the core config

Takes in the following parameters

Name Data Type Parameter Type Required Description
KeysToUpdate Dictionary<Type,Dictionary`2> Not Set! Not Set! No ApiMember attribute! Please ask a Dev to add an [ApiMember] attribute

TypeScript Example

var dto = <api.UpdateAppSettingsDto>{
	KeysToUpdate: this.someValue1, // Dictionary<Type,Dictionary`2> 
};
this.cvApi.jSConfigs.UpdateAppSettings(dto).then(r => {
	if (!r || !r.data) {
		// Error State
		return;
	}
	this.something = r.data;
}).catch(reason => console.error(reason));
